                  "title": "Comment \u201cTOPICS\u201d to get a full guide on what you actually need to learn.\n\nRAG is the first thing everyone learns. It\u2019s also where most people stop.\n\nAnd I get why. It\u2019s the topic all over your feed right now, so it feels like the whole job. But when 1,700+ real AI engineering job descriptions were reverse-engineered, RAG was one line item in a much longer list.\n\nIf you already know how to build software, here\u2019s the AI-specific layer that actually gets you hired:\n\nAgents and orchestration. Chaining tools, managing state, and building workflows that survive production. LangGraph, MCP, the full stack.\n\nEvaluation. If you can\u2019t measure whether your system got better or worse, you\u2019re guessing. This is what separates a demo from a real product.\n\nLLMOps. Deployment, monitoring, versioning, cost control. The unglamorous work that keeps you employed.\n\nSafety and guardrails. Companies won\u2019t ship what they can\u2019t trust, so knowing how to handle this is a hiring signal on its own.\n\nML foundations.",
